gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Knicks 126, Raptors 100
gameRecap.excerpt: The Knicks defeated the Raptors, 126-100. Jalen Brunson led the way for the Knicks with 38 points (5-11 3pt. FG) and nine assists, while Julius Randle added 18 points, 16 rebounds and 10 assists in the victory, his 1st triple-double of the season and 14th of his career. Former Knicks RJ Barrett (20 points, eight rebounds) and Immanuel Quickley (12 points, season-high 11 assists) combined for 32 points for the Raptors in the losing effort. The Knicks have won three straight games as they improve to 26-17 on the season, while the Raptors fall to 16-27.
